## 📖 About

**Mine Sweeper** is a classic logic puzzle game. It features a grid of clickable tiles, with hidden _mines_ randomly placed throughout the board.

The objective is to clear the entire board without _detonating_ any mines. Clues are provided by numbers indicating how many neighboring tiles contain mines.

---

## ✨ Features

- Customizable grid sizes
- Multiple difficulty levels
- Intuitive UI
- High scores tracking

---

## 🎮 How to Play

1. Click tiles to reveal them.
2. Numbers indicate how many mines are adjacent.
3. Right-click to flag suspected mines.
4. Clear the board without detonating a mine to win!

---

## 🚀 Installation & Setup Guide

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/mondragonjake/Mine-Sweeper.git
cd Mine-Sweeper

2. Open the Project in VS Code
Ensure you have the Java Extension Pack installed in VS Code.

Open the src folder using VS Code.

Navigate to Main.java inside the src directory.

3. Run the Application
Open Main.java in VS Code.

Run it using:

The Run Java button in the top right corner of VS Code, or

Press the F6 key (default keybind for Run Java).

4. Build a JAR File (Optional)
If you want to build a .jar file:

Press Ctrl + Shift + P to open the Command Palette.

Search for and select Java: Export Jar.

Choose Main as the main class.

Select all necessary files when prompted.

Confirm by clicking OK.

This will generate a Mine-Sweeper.jar file in your project directory.

5. Run the JAR File
You can run the JAR in one of the following ways:

Option A: Command Line
bash
Copy
Edit
java -jar Mine-Sweeper.jar
Option B: Double-click (GUI)
Double-click the Mine-Sweeper.jar file (Java Runtime Environment must be installed).

⚠️ Important: Use Java 21 or later. The application will not run on earlier versions.
